article.description: Reginald Johnson scored a career-high 35 points and Hampton overcame a 22-point second-half deficit -- scoring 54 points in the period -- to beat Northern Arizona in double overtime 98-94 on Wedn
article.headline: Hampton beats Northern Arizona in 2OT, 98-94
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Reginald Johnson scored a career-high 35 points and Hampton overcame a 22-point second-half deficit -- scoring 54 points in the period -- to beat Northern Arizona in double overtime 98-94 on Wednesday night. Hampton made six free throws in the second overtime, while the Lumberjacks managed just Kris Yanku's layup with 2 seconds left. The teams combined to shoot 1 of 10 in the frame. The Lumberjacks led 42-26 at intermission. Corey Brown's dunk 1:04 into the second pushed the lead over 20. Hampton chipped away though, and Brian Darden's 3-pointer with 57 seconds in regulation forced overtime. Northern Arizona went up by five in the first OT, but Darden hit a jumper, then his defensive rebound led to Johnson's 3-pointer with 11 seconds left to prompt the second session. Darden finished with 22 points for Hampton (3-3). Yanku led Northern Arizona (2-5) with 25 points and was perfect on 16 free-throw attempts.
